FAQs on Indian Embassy Attestation
Can someone submit my documents on my behalf at the Indian Embassy?
Yes. You can authorize a trusted person to submit your documents. They must carry a valid ID and a signed authorization letter. Our team at Indexauh also handles submissions on your behalf, ensuring your documents reach the embassy safely and on time.

Are translations required for Indian documents before attestation?
Some documents, especially regional language certificates, may need certified English translations. Educational or legal documents issued in English usually do not need translation. We guide you on which documents require translation to save time and prevent delays.

Can attested documents be used for multiple purposes in the UAE?
Yes. Once documents are attested by the Indian Embassy and UAE MOFA, they can be used for family visas, employment, property matters, or legal purposes. We make sure your documents are attested correctly so they are accepted for all intended uses.

What happens if a document is rejected by the embassy or MOFA?
Rejection usually happens if the document is incomplete, not verified in the correct order, or contains errors. Our team reviews every document carefully before submission to prevent rejections. In case of any issue, we guide you step by step to correct it.

Do you provide free pickup and delivery for attestation services in UAE?
Absolutely. Indexauh offers free pickup and delivery to make the process easy and convenient. Your documents are collected securely, attested, and returned safely to your doorstep.